Diagnosis.
The species is characterized by: 
1
) small to medium size (SVL 
32.1–54.1 mm
in males and 
30.4
– 50.0 mm in females); 
2
) broad head, dorso-ventrally depressed (HW/SVL 
54
%); 
3
) thigh length plus tibia length corresponding to more than 
90
% of SVL); 
4
) gular region light brown; 
5
) ventral surface cream with scattered brown dots; 
6
) contact between nasal bones in their rostral extremities (

Fig. 
4

); 
7
) wide contact between nasal and frontoparietal bones in their posterior extremities (

Fig. 
4

); 
8
) iliac projection corresponding to more than 
50
% of ilium diameter.

Geographical distribution. The new species is known from the municipalities of Angra dos Reis, Itaguaí, Mangaratiba and Paraty in Rio de Janeiro state, Brazil (
Fig. 7
).
